com.ibm.team.build.common.model

Interface IBuildRequest

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAuditable, IAuditableHandle, IBuildItem, IBuildItemHandle, IBuildRequestHandle, IItem, IItemHandle, IManagedItem, IManagedItemHandle

    public interface IBuildRequest
extends IBuildRequestHandle, IAuditable, IBuildItem
    Represents a request to perform an action on a build result or build definition.
    Since:
    0.5

      • getCreatedMilliseconds

        long getCreatedMilliseconds()
        Deprecated. Use getCreated() instead.
        Retrieves the time the request was made as the number of milliseconds since Jan 1, 1970 GMT. It's used to support ordering the requests in the queue. This is a workaround for bug 7021, which keeps us from using getCreated() on the client.
        Returns:
        The time the request was made.

      • getBuildDefinitionProperties

        java.util.Map getBuildDefinitionProperties()
        Get a copy of the build definition properties from the request's build definition instance.
        Returns:
        A map of the property names and values. The map keys are the property names (type String). The map values are the property values (type String). The returned map will be empty if there are no build definition properties. The returned map will be null if the buildDefinitionInstance was not fetched as part of this item.

      • getPotentialHandlers

        java.util.List<IBuildEngineHandle> getPotentialHandlers()
        Returns the handles of build engines that may handle this request. If empty, the engines supporting the build definition are used.
        Returns:
        The handles of build engines that may handle this request.
        Since:
        0.8
